  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Citizen Watch in Diffa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">On February 6, 2015, the Diffa region has become the subject of a military campaign confronting the forces of defense and national security and the Islamic sect BOKO Haram, after the group had been active in Nigeria for years. Niger was receiving huge numbers of Nigerian refugees already in the Diffa region. Within weeks of clashes, hundreds of deaths, injuries and thousands of displaced people are registered. The region is in a state of emergency and thereby became a military zone with all that it implies: upheaval in the lives of people who are already burdened by poverty and chronic food insecurity.
On this basis, the Alternative Espaces Citoyens decided to implement this project to address three (3) main problems, namely:

- (I) the risk of misuseof the legal exception can result in massive violations of fundamental human rights of people living in the region and the non-observance of international humanitarian law (IHL) by belligerents :
- (Ii) The absence of a mechanism for citizen monitoring and warning involving local stakeholders (local elected officials, communities, local organizations):
- (Iii) low valuation and use of the potential of community radio in security problem management
The overall objective of the project is to contribute to the preservation of democracy and peace in Niger,through a better defense and protection of fundamental rights of the people in times of armed conflict. Specifically, the objectives of the project are:

(I) -Establish and make it operational by 2016ACitizens Watch mechanism, to share information and alert public opinion on the evolution of the situation of human and humanitarian rights in the Diffa region.
- (Ii) - Conduct advocacy and lobbying actions to bring the government and its partners, by2016, to take concrete measures to support the consequences of armed conflict on the lives of people especially in terms of access to basic services (health, food, education, water, sanitation and hygiene).</narrative>
  </description>
  <participating-org role="4" type="24">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Alternatives Espace Citoyens, AEC</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Alternatives Espaces Citoyens was founded in Niger in September 2001. The initiator was Groupe Alternative, an NGO working on culture and the media and connected to the journal Alternative. Alternatives Espaces Citoyens fights for democratic values through civil education. For this purpose, it uses its radio station in Niamey, and its so-called study centres spread all over the country.
Vision : a society based on the values of democracy, social justice, solidarity and preservation of the environment, where fundamental freedoms , human rights , equity and equality between men and women are scrupulously respected .

The association aims to &quot; work towards the emergence of an open, democratic and social society , based on equality of human rights, a new partnership between men and women, solidarity between people in an healthy environment. &quot;

The objectives of the association are:
- promote, defend and contributeto the effectiveness of fundamental human rights and individual and collective freedoms ;
- build spaces of resistance, convergenceof social movements and alternatives to neoliberal policies ;
- Develop initiatives for citizen control of public action at national and local levels;
- Promote the rights, citizen participation and empowerment of women and vulnerable groups;
- contribute to the improvement of the environment and the protection of public goods , particularly water , forests , land and genetic endowment;
- Promote access , development and innovative use of media and information technologies and communication .

Alternatives Espaces Citoyens is a major actor in the emerging critical wing of the civil society of Niger.  Alternatives Espaces Citoyens is the co-initiator of the Social Forum of Niger (FSN), and manages its secretariat.</narrative>
